body.head: A Bibliography of TEI Council Minutes
body.p: The following is a list of TEI Technical Council meetings and teleconferences, with links to the meeting minutes.

Each meeting has been given a unique identifier in the form TCMddd, continuing the numbering used in the original TEI Vault. This is used as the value of the xml:id attribute on each bibl (bibliographic entry). In addition, each meeting has been given an identifier in the form yyyy-mm derived from the date that the meeting began. For the very small number of cases where more than one meeting took place in a month, the second one has a suffix b (for bis). This meeting identifier is supplied as the value of the n attribute on the meeting element, and also forms the base part of the filename for each transcribed version of the minutes.

Each set of minutes is available in at least one of the following forms
TEI P5 From the github repository 163 documents re-encoded in a simple TEI P5-conformant scheme, from 2023-04 to 2002-01
In Word Press HTML Online at the TEI-C website 163 files in WordPress HTML, from 2023-04 to 2002-01
TEI Legacy Legacy TEI format from Internet Archive or elsewhere 39 files in TEI P4 or P5, from 2008-10 to 2002-01

The P5 archival format used is described by a TEI customisation called tcMins, documentation and definition of which is a work in progress. A| preliminary (auto-generated) version of the ODD source is visible at current tcMins ODD.

The archival files were produced as follows
For all minutes from 2009 to date (with one exception), the most recently edited "official" version still available is stored on the current TEI-C website in Word Press format. This was downloaded using curl, and reprocessed to produce the TEI P5 version using simple XSLT scripts.
For meetings held before 2009, I was able to locate a TEI XML (or SGML) version of the proceedings, in the Internet Archive, in my own files, or in the TEI-C website's "Vault". I did some minor retagging of these to make them conform to the TCMins schema, and also to reduce (slightly) the variety of encoding praxis demonstrated.
For some reason, presumably accidental, minutes of the Council's FTF meeting in Koln in February 2018 are not currently available on the TEI-C website. The archival version listed here is derived from a copy of the Google Docs draft document preserved in the Council's private archive.

In the list below, the link "TEI P5" displays a formatted version of the archived file, using CETEICean to render it. The "Raw TEI P5" and "TEI Legacy" links point directly to source files stored in the Github repository. The link "[on website]" points directly to the Word Press version currently published at the TEI-C website,
